2 (4) Option 4. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Section or any
3 other law to the contrary, any retiree of the system, who has been retired for at
4 least one year from the effective date of his retirement, may be reemployed to
5 fill certain critical shortage positions within the Department of Public Safety
6 and Corrections, corrections services, subject to all of the following:
7 (a) For the purposes of this Subsection, a "critical shortage position" is
8 defined as a full-time position for which the Department of Public Safety and
9 Corrections, corrections services, has advertised in accordance with Louisiana
10 civil service rules and has received an insufficient number of suitable applicants.
11 The secretary shall determine candidate suitability based on operational needs
12 and institutional requirements. Critical shortage positions shall include but are
13 not limited to the following full-time positions, as certified by the secretary of
14 the Department of Public Safety and Corrections based on fluctuating critical
15 needs:
16 (i) Major.
17 (ii) Captain.
18 (iii) Lieutenant.
19 (iv) Specialized sergeant-master.
20 (v) Cadet, sergeant, or master sergeant.
21 (vi) Registered nurse.
22 (vii) Licensed practical nurse.
23 (viii) Social worker.
24 (b) Prior to the posting of a critical shortage position pursuant to this
25 Paragraph, the secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections
26 shall certify in writing the need to fill the vacancy.
27 (c) The secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections
28 shall annually review and certify in writing the continued necessity of filling the
29 critical shortage position or the continued reemployment of the retiree in the
30 position.
