1 (d) A retiree reemployed in a critical shortage position pursuant to this
2 Subsection shall be entitled to receive his full retirement benefits during the
3 period of reemployment.
4 (e) During the period of reemployment in a critical shortage position,
5 both the reemployed retiree and the Department of Public Safety and
6 Corrections, corrections services, shall make contributions to the retirement
7 system as required by the system. However, the reemployed retiree shall not
8 earn additional service credit or accrue any additional retirement benefits.
9 Upon termination of reemployment, the retiree shall be refunded the employee
10 contributions made during the period of reemployment, without interest.
11 Employer contributions made during this period shall be retained by the
12 retirement system.
13 (f) No member of this system who retires based on a disability shall
14 return to service pursuant to the provisions of this Paragraph. Disability
15 retirees shall be governed by the provisions of this Chapter applicable to
16 disability retirees.
17 * * *
18 Section 2. The cost of this Act, if any, shall be funded with additional employer
19 contributions in compliance with Article X, Section 29(F) of the Constitution of Louisiana.
